- Ryukyu Pirates - A more historical one, imagining a scenario where the still very young Ryukyu Kingdom falls to pirates before it becomes a Ming tributary. In game the three Ryukyu provinces usually unify early into the Ryukyu Kingdom which is an existing formable in the vanilla game. However you can not take them over, or spawn there as pirates, so I think it would make sense to remove the ruling family, and either establish a new, piracy focused Ryukyu Kingdom, or turn it into a Pirate Republic.
- Kaidō Bakufu - Less historic, but more fitting for a large pirate nation. Kaidō translates to "road" or "sea route", the latter of which was often used for maritime routes and trade lines, while Bakufu was a name for the Tokugawa government after uniting Japan. So technically it's something like Sea/Maritime Shogunate, which I feel is fitting name for a pirate republic that successfully takes advantage of the Sengoku conflict, and defeats some of the splintered clans to proclaim it's own Shogunate. If you want to stick to english names, "Shogunate of the Seas" is a good alternative I believe.
